I immediately called the restaurant to let them know that I was not satisfied with the food I spent almost $100 on and drove 45 minutes for. The host was the only person I was in communication with and she let me know the kitchen said it wasn’t their fault my food was bland and I shouldn’t have made modifications to my order. Also, the manager told her to offer me a jar of sauce for my inconvenience. A $10 jar of sauce. The next day the host (still not communication with the manager) offered me a discount on my next order so I guess I’m expected to spend MORE money and hope they get the next order correct. That sucks because I literally love this place and I was trying to support the restaurants I love during this pandemic while we’re watching so many businesses close their doors. Very unfortunate and disappointing.

We went to the Crab Pad for a special event.  It's a Cajun style Seafood boil restaurant where you get down and dirty with your food. (Yes, that means you eat with your hands).  It was great to share a table with my old friends and make new ones.  We started off with a choice of limeade juice boxes of several flavors from the Crab Pad, which were then made into adults only juice boxes by adding a shot of rum or vodka.  The restaurant is BYOB, this was special just for us.  We had our own long table, and when they started to pile food on the table, no one knew just what to expect next.  The rice, corn, potatoes, sausage and green beans were plentiful and more than enough for everyone.  We each received a bag full of shrimp, crawfish and crab legs, with your choice of mild, medium or spicy seasonings.  You will be able to choose your own combination from the menu.  At the end of the evening, we were treated to ice cream bars from Milk & Wood.  You pick a flavorful bar, drizzle it with syrup and top it off with your choice of 9 different toppings.  There were some very unusual flavors, but, I had the mint oreo bar.  This was a wonderful dessert, and will be a great treat on a warm weather day.  Theresa the owner was a wonderful hostess and made sure everyone had enough food and drinks flowing throughout the evening.  I highly recommend the Crab Pad, the food is delicious, prices are reasonable, the owner is awesome and the service can't be beat. Literally the best, hippest, and coolest restaurant in the area. Super affordable, unique, and fantastic idea. Execution done incredibly. Food is to die for, get the garlic noodles, BISCUITS (garlic jam on top), and shrimp bag (combo 3).
Not what you expect but more. Great atmosphere a dam good time!
Get your hands dirty and dig in. Limited selection of food but good. Friendly and great waitstaff.  This place is cash-only.
The choosing and ordering can be a bit overwhelming.  However the seafood is excellent and the service relatively quick. You will need that bib.
First time here and all I got to say was it was AMAZING! Def will be coming back
OMG! Sooooo delicious! BYOB
If I could give this place 10 stars I would. I love it here from the king crab legs to the green tea kit kat Popsicle. This place is awesome!!!!

Made a 4pm reservation for Father's day, not crowded and got sat around 3:30. Got a pound each of snow crab, whole shrimp and mussels with mild everything sauce. Sauce wasn't too heavy and a side of hot sauce was perfect heat. Fairly priced except the rice. It's $2 for like an 8oz styrofoam cups and they don't fill it all the way- this is a big deal for my family.  Best part is the have milk & wood, which is a perfect dessert. All in all, a great experience!
Not a big seafood person but went with family to try it out if it had at least more than 2 items on menu for the home seafood lover it would be great. My family loved it
Food is delicious and fresh. Lot's of variety, a bit pricey. Pretty small inside so it could get very crowded at times.  BYOB.
Wow. Amazing seafood!

To be a seafood place the wings are the bomb. I go for the shrimp and the crawfish, cajun style spicy hot. You can't go wrong with adding some little extra in the bag like corn and potatos. I have visited this plce more than 3 times, and I have never had an issue with the staff, the food, and of course the price.
Amazing food and a good time!
The food is just delicious. Medium spicy Crab Pad style is the way to go!

WONDERFUL !! Excellent !! I felt so so so Loved!! I went there for a birthday dinner; The host was very welcoming and my waitress  Cat was the BEST waitress I ever had at a restaurant EVER. she was so sweet, very inform, great energy etc. I can go on and on I was OVER satisfied with the service and food and my over all FIRST TIME experience was the best ever !

Crab and shellfish in a very large plastic bag full of sauce. You can really only taste the sauce. This is incredibly messy, and not because it's crab but because of the bag full of sauce. You will need to dig through this bag to pull out your food. You'll only get a flimsy plastic fork or knife if you ask (none on the table).  The food is okay - the 'crab pad' sauce is oily and spicy. We order two bags and they put the wrong items in the wrong bag/sauce.  For 5 adults, eating out of a plastic bag, we spent $200.  If you think you'll enjoy the experience then it might be worth a visit. If you just want good seafood, pass and go to a regular restaurant (with silverware).
Fun, messy, delicious, and sensual!
Great food, great service.

We went to eat dessert first (got the make your own popsicle) which wasn't bad, but well overpriced at $5 for 1 tiny pop. Was still going to stick it out for dinner until I found a shrimp antenna in the middle of my popsicle. Left mad and wont be back.

LOVE this place! BYOB?!?! Heck yessss!!! Everyone gets to eat like they're in their own living room without cleaning up!! And flavors?!?! You're guaranteed to ENJOY every bite.... finger-licking good!!
Good place and their spices are unique but it is a change from other places like this.

Just ate here last week... honestly one of the best meals I've ever had. Now there's a lot to consider in deciding to eat here. First off, it's a mess. NO way around that, but it is so worth it and I believe that's part of what makes it so great. So don't go there on a first date, it won't end well. That being said, the food is out of this world. It may be a little pricey, but it's sea food in Chicago, and for what you get, it's well worth it. The whole shrimp was my favorite, but everything was outstanding. Solid desert as well! The staff was very kind and helpful, and you can't beat BYOB. I can not wait to return to this place.
Great food, great atmosphere, great server!
Great atmosphere, everything was on point and our waitress Kiaralyn was fabulous!!!!

Everything was amazing. I can't wait to go back. Thank you to our server for helping us make all the right choices. We ended up with 2 lobster tails, headless shrimp, mussels, crab legs, corn, and potatoes. Lots of food, but we didn't struggle ad it was so delicious and fresh.  I agree with server that the combo of all 3 sauces was the best option for the bag. Wear your apron, and don't forget its b.y.o.b so bring your 6 pack.
Great food, fun atmosphere, great service, BYOB! The popsicle stand is amazing as well. Just an FYI, the medium spicy = pretty darn spicy!

It was our last night in Chicago before my group and I had to drive back home to our home state. Parking was a pain in the ass of course. Everything tasted good! The new England clam chowder was very nice and thick, the cheese was kinda overwhelming, but otherwise than that it was fine! I swear, we had more sauce rather than the seafood. The snow crab didn't even have any meat in them, the meat didn't even fill half of the shell. We got half a quarter of snow crab leggs. Disappointed! One time experience is good enough.
Great seafood selection at a reasonable price.  Get the noodles with sauce.  Definitely worth it to soak up the juices.
Great servers, Awesome Food and Lots of Happy people enjoying the Chefs Treats!  A Yum Yum dinning experience.

Wait staff was fun and energetic, well lit, very clean, very friendly place. The well priced seafood was delicious, my mother and son enjoyed it. I recommend this place for good seafood it would've gotten a 5 stars but it took an hour to get the food.
1st the customer service is the best, 2nd the food is amazing, 3rd its byob..... One of the best crab places I've ever tasted!! My all time favorite place to eat.

The food lacked seasoning big time. All the seafood is priced by the pound but most of the is has more shell than meat so you end up paying for a bunch of garbage. I like the concept but the execution needs work. The fries were good.
Pretty much the same experience as The Angry Crab

the seafood here is pretty fresh but bland, you have to really peel it and leave it in the sauce for a few minutes before eating. the sauce is a bit too oily, especially the crab pad sauce. one thing i really like about the sauce is it's filled with garlic.  there's an icecream bar (milk & wood), but we ordered a bit too much seafood to have space left over for the icecream.
This place is a lot of fun. Good place to go for a date or with friends.
Great food and byob!
Amazing seafood, wings and garlic noodles.  BYOB makes this place even better.  Sunday and Monday they have 69 cent wings.  Never a wait.
Food is amazing!
Love this place! There is a similar one in Uptown so I was happy to find this when I moved to Logan. The popsicle bar was a really cool & unique touch too!
Great crab and mussels. Excellent staff
If you like seafood, you need to come here.

Prepare to get messy! We had the clams, shrimp, Cajun fries, wings, and a popsicle. Oddly enough, I highly recommend the wings! They were huge with excellent flavor. As for the seafood, the shrimp seemed like a better value as the clam shells account for most of the weight when ordering by the pound. The staff was friendly and the BYOB was a plus.

I'm so glad this place is nearby.  I really like the concept of ordering seafood by the pound, I'm very comfortable with that measure.  My son added the spaghetti to the order, I was so pleased with the end result.  It can be very messy, the hand sink in the dining room is a smart amenity.  I'm not sure about the prices, I'm not familiar with the scale.  The Popsicle dessert option was cool too.  I was there during the day when there were only four tables, and it was open for about one week.  My server was MIA for a bit, she was on her phone within eyesight so I knew she was close by despite being into her social media.  That was minor.  I fully expect I will be back, with a seafood loving crowd.
Great service and food, very casual and friendly place.
Very new place, and it's not too bad. Hope it sticks around the hood
Outstanding! Quality seafood and sides. Noodles are a fun complement. Love the seasoning options. Ice cream popsicles are legit!
